STEPS TO INSTALL THE UVMULTIFIT PACKAGE:


1.- Compile the C++ module. Just run:

    python setup.py build_ext --inplace
    
    After this step, the file "_uvmultimodel.so" should have 
    been created.

2.- Copy the "uvmultifit.py", "GUI_All_PySide.py", and 
    "_uvmultimodel.so" files into a destination directory. 
    The name of this directory could be, e.g.

         $HOME/.casa/Nordic_Tools/uvfit

3.- Add the name of this directory into the CASA path. For 
    this step, you must edit the file $HOME/.casa/init.py
    and add:

    import sys
    sys.path.append("$HOME/.casa/Nordic_Tools/uvfit")

4.- Load the module into CASA. You can do it from the init.py 
    file or from inside CASA. To import the module from the 
    init file, add the following line at the end of your 
    $HOME/.casa/init.py:

    import uvmultifit as uvm

    To import the module from CASA, just execute the same 
    line in a script, or at the CASA prompt.

5.- ENJOY!


Any feedback and bug report should be sent either to the ARC 
Nordic Node (contact@nordic-alma.se) or to the source maintainer
(ivan.marti-vidal@chalmers.se).


